## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="2f506-113">Use o <xref:System.ServiceModel.MessageBodyMemberAttribute.Order%2A> propriedade para especificar o local de um membro de dados no elemento do corpo SOAP.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2f506-113">Use the <xref:System.ServiceModel.MessageBodyMemberAttribute.Order%2A> property to specify the location of a data member in the SOAP body element.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2f506-114">O valor não precisa ser consecutivos, porque ele não representa a posição do membro, apenas a chave de classificação.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2f506-114">The value is not required to be consecutive, because it does not represent the position of the member, only the sorting key.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2f506-115">A ordem dos elementos do corpo é alfabética por padrão.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2f506-115">The order of the body elements is alphabetical by default.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2f506-116">A semântica dessa propriedade é o mesmo que a semântica do <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.DataMemberAttribute.Order%2A> propriedade.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2f506-116">The semantics of this property are the same as the semantics of the <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.DataMemberAttribute.Order%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="2f506-117">O seguinte exemplo de código usa o <xref:System.ServiceModel.MessageBodyMemberAttribute.Order%2A> propriedade para serializar o `sourceAccount` valor pela primeira vez, o `targetAccount` valor segundo e o `amount` valor de terceiros.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2f506-117">The following code example uses the <xref:System.ServiceModel.MessageBodyMemberAttribute.Order%2A> property to serialize the `sourceAccount` value first, the `targetAccount` value second and the `amount` value third.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2f506-118">Se o <xref:System.ServiceModel.MessageBodyMemberAttribute.Order%2A> propriedade não for usada, o `amount` valor é serializado pela primeira vez.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2f506-118">If the <xref:System.ServiceModel.MessageBodyMemberAttribute.Order%2A> property is not used, the `amount` value is serialized first.</span></span>  
  
```  
[MessageContract]  
public class BankingTransaction  
{  
  [MessageHeader] public Operation operation;  
  [MessageBodyMember(Order=1)] public Account sourceAccount;  
  [MessageBodyMember(Order=2)] public Account targetAccount;  
  [MessageBodyMember(Order=3)] public int amount;  
}  
```
